<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="561" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,2000,2025]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="561" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,2000,2025]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males differ from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: apicolateral processes of tergite IX elongate, each bearing two setae, parameres fused on proximal 1/3, aedeagus with seed-like medial prongs, lateral prongs lightly sclerotized with setose apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
